# Implementation Plan: Authentication & User API

This plan outlines the first step of creating our API layer, starting with expanding the `User` entity to support full profile details and implementing the Authentication Controller and Service (`Register` and `Login`).

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Domain Layer (Entity Extension)

The current C# [User.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Domain/Entities/User.cs) is a stub and is missing fields displayed in the ER Diagram (such as `FirstName`, `LastName`, `MobileNo`, `Gender`, `DOB`, etc.). We will add these fields to make the authentication payload valid.

#### [MODIFY] [User.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Domain/Entities/User.cs)
- Add `FirstName`, `LastName` (Required, MaxLength 100).
- Add `MobileNo` (Required, MaxLength 20).
- Add `Gender` (MaxLength 10).
- Add `DOB` (DateTime).
- Add `IsEmailVerified`, `IsMobileVerified` (bool, default false).
- Add `CreatedDate`, `UpdatedDate`, `LastLoginDate` (DateTime).

#### [MODIFY] [ApplicationDbContext.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Persistent/Context/ApplicationDbContext.cs)
- Configure new fields in the `User` entity mappings.

---

### 2. Application Layer (Auth Service)

We will implement the service that handles user registration (hashing passwords, validating roles, checking email duplicates) and login (comparing hashes and generating JWT claims).

#### [NEW] [IAuthService.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Application/Services/IAuthService.cs)
Declares contracts:
- `Task<AuthResponseDto> RegisterAsync(RegisterDto registerDto);`
- `Task<AuthResponseDto> LoginAsync(LoginDto loginDto);`

#### [NEW] [AuthService.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Application/Services/AuthService.cs)
Implements:
- Role checks (validating whether selected role is Patient, Doctor, Admin).
- Safe password hashing (using BCrypt or similar standard PBKDF2 hash, or standard ASP.NET Identity hashing helper).
- Querying and inserting users using `ApplicationDbContext`.
- Mock/Basic JWT Token generation (to be fully secured in the authentication phase later).

---

### 3. API Layer (Controllers)

#### [NEW] [AuthController.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Controllers/AuthController.cs)
Exposes endpoints:
- `POST /api/auth/register` (returns `AuthResponseDto`)
- `POST /api/auth/login` (returns `AuthResponseDto`)
- Handled safely by our previously registered `GlobalExceptionHandler`.

#### [MODIFY] [Program.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Program.cs)
- Register `IAuthService` with `builder.Services.AddScoped<IAuthService, AuthService>();`.

